{
  "stem": "23428.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Must have been very close to the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So, from then on, I was separated from my brother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Otherwise, all right, now this-- this-- this infection proved to be a godsend because, first of all, it kept me inside when it was extremely cold on the outside.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, ?] these work details had to work at minus 30, minus 35 degrees Centigrade.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Up in Silesia, it gets very cold and snow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I was lying on my straw on a blanket, being visited by the-- by the physician of the block-- physicians of the block.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Now, it turns out that these physicians-- one of these physicians happened to be a neighbor of my grandmother's in Berlin, also an [? upper-classy ?] German who knew my grandmother and, obviously, also realized I was a kid and whatnot.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And-- and-- and both he and the-- Paul Self, the guy who beat up the Portuguese and a number of other Frenchmen in his-- in his surroundings-- also adopted me because I spoke fluent French.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That had to do for-- with the-- with the Belgian history.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So-- so-- so they made me into a male nurse, where my job was to wash operation-- to wash blood and pus off operation tables.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And-- and not a-- not really a-- a fun job.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But, again, it was warm.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Moreover, it gave me two spoons full of soup in the evening, rather than what ordinary citizens got, which was one spoonful or one ladle spoon, one ladle full of soup.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Got two ladles.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Well, that obviously prolonged your life.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So-- so being a male nurse there, obviously, was a-- was a-- was a-- was-- was one of the elements of my survival.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, all of them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everybody was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
